Code of Conduct
Our Pledge

In the interest of fostering an open and welcoming environment, we as contributors and maintainers pledge to make participation in this project free from harassment and discrimination. We value respect, kindness, and constructive collaboration.

Expected Behavior

Be respectful and considerate in all interactions.

Use inclusive language and avoid offensive comments.

Offer constructive feedback and focus on ideas, not individuals.

Follow the project guidelines and maintain professionalism.

Acknowledge and respect the work of others.

Unacceptable Behavior

Harassment, intimidation, or abusive language.

Discrimination based on age, gender, sexual orientation, disability, race, religion, or nationality.

Deliberate sabotage of the project or its community.

Public criticism of othersâ€™ contributions in a hostile manner.

Reporting Issues

If you experience or witness unacceptable behavior:

Reach out to the project maintainer via email or GitHub issues.

Provide as much detail as possible (e.g., screenshots, URLs, usernames).

All reports will be handled confidentially and respectfully.

Enforcement

Project maintainers may take appropriate actions, including:

Issuing warnings

Removing disruptive contributors

Reporting to platform authorities if necessary

Acknowledgment

By participating in this project, you agree to adhere to this Code of Conduct. Our goal is to create a welcoming, supportive, and productive environment for everyone.